snippet.textDisplay:
Hey guys,
 
People from Odisha may be quite aware of the title line. Yes, coke studio is releasing the Rangabati remix version . We all feel very proud about it, don't we?
 
Having said that I wanted to convey congrats to my aunt Miss Krishna Patel and Dr. Jitendra Harpal on this and I called them and what did I get to hear, they do not know have any knowledge about it.
 
The singers, the composers, the lyricist the song writer, they had a call and they informed that they were totally unaware of what coke studio is doing with the song. Being the famous singers for the world renowned song Rangabati the feet throb of Odisha, they were not even informed about the song being performed in some part of India. Let alone the singing part, they were not even given the credits to it.
 
Do you guys see the mention of them on the title, on the page, anywhere. It is a singer's pride to proudly say that he/she has brought to India. 
 
However  they being left out of the scene and someone else singing the song on behalf of them , without their permission( no offense to the singer), isn't that shameful on their part. The singers who have practised, toured all over the world to represent a small part of India and indirectly representing India through the time they learnt singing.. be it russia or Indonesia.
 
Having said that I wanted to bring this to the notice of the much respected Sona mohapatra, being a child of odisha should she not feel obligated to have offered the song to the singers rather than singing it herself.
 
When I tried to reach out to them being the celebrity, which they obviously are I could not contact them directly and so the messages went to the Spam box. But the shocking part was when I posted a comment to the Trailer posted by " Sona Mohapatra" it was removed after a whie.
 
Such respect I had hardly ever seen.
 
The singers are ashamed when they got a call from MTV and the odia news about it asking them " How they feel about it?" . They answered .." we are upset".
 
Whoa such a tribute guys, the people who put their soul into the song are ashamed of this.
 
I request you my friends, please share this. Its a shame people bringing price to your state and nation are upset about such a thing.
 
PS: The song writer does not even know his song is being used as  RAP
